quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  25,3,"And they have taken apart from Him gods who do not create anything, but are themselves created, and who possess for themselves neither harm nor benefit, and have no power over life or death or resurrection."
  25,4,"Moreover, those who have denied said, “This is nothing but a fabrication that he has forged, while other people have helped him with it.” They have certainly come forth with injustice and falsehood."
  25,5,"And they said, “Legends of the ancients that he has sought to be written down; thus they are dictated to him morning and evening.”"
  25,6,"Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “It was sent down by the One Who knows the Secret in the heavens and the earth; indeed, He has always been Oft-Forgiving, Bestowing of mercy.”"
  25,7,"And they said, “What sort of messenger is this who eats food and walks in marketplaces? If only an angel had been sent down to him to be a warner alongside him,"
  25,8,"or if a treasure were to be cast to him, or if he had a garden from which <span class=""h"">he eats<sup foot_note=""80685"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>.” And the unjust ones said, “You<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>are only following a bewitched man.”"
  25,9,"Look<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>how they have set forth parables for you and gone astray, so they cannot find a way."
  25,10,"Supremely Blessed be the One Who, if He so willed, would provide you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>with better than that—Gardens beneath which rivers flow—<span class=""h"">and make<sup foot_note=""80686"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>for you palaces."
  25,11,"Rather, they have considered the Hour to be a lie, and We have prepared a blaze for those who have disbelieved in the Hour."
